{"question_id": "Q005", "question": "How do the encoder and decoder stacks differ in the Transformer architecture?", "ground_truth": "The encoder has repeated layers with self-attention and feed-forward sublayers, while the decoder adds an extra sublayer that attends over the encoder output and also uses masked self-attention so it cannot look ahead to future positions.", "category": "intra_paper_comparison", "difficulty": "medium", "policy": "maddpg_ceb", "data_source": "live_llm", "final_status": "accepted", "final_answer": "The encoder and decoder stacks differ in that the decoder inserts a third sub-layer, which performs multi-head attention over the output of the encoder stack, in addition to the two sub-layers in each encoder layer.", "token_f1": 0.3333, "rouge_l": 0.2338, "correctness": 0.3333, "faithfulness": 1.0, "citation_support": 1.0, "source_precision": 0.3333, "source_recall": 1.0, "verification_pass": 1, "unsupported_claims": 0, "latency_seconds": 194.59, "num_llm_calls": 3, "token_usage": 3543, "num_steps": 4, "trace": [{"step": 1, "agent": "retriever", "action": "hybrid_rerank", "params": {"dense_sparse_weight": 0.5378687791526318, "top_k": 17, "rerank_threshold": 0.6971522122621536, "source_diversity": 0.2435663938522339}, "reward": -0.1206, "done": false}, {"step": 2, "agent": "grader", "action": "strict_filter", "params": {"relevance_threshold": 0.8260274231433868, "evidence_keep_ratio": 0.7374843060970306, "strictness_score": 0.7720123529434204}, "reward": -0.3115, "done": false}, {"step": 3, "agent": "generator", "action": "generate_answer", "params": {"temperature": 0.7456640899181366, "citation_strictness": 0.3304324895143509, "max_tokens": 618, "answer_detail_level": 0.404483325779438}, "reward": -0.4213, "done": false}, {"step": 4, "agent": "verifier", "action": "verify_answer", "params": {"support_threshold": 0.6769298315048218, "confidence_threshold": 0.4492737762629986}, "reward": -0.148, "done": true}]}
{"question_id": "Q006", "question": "How does BERT's masked language model objective differ from next sentence prediction?", "ground_truth": "Masked language modeling predicts masked tokens from context within the input, while next sentence prediction trains the model to decide whether sentence B truly follows sentence A.", "category": "intra_paper_comparison", "difficulty": "medium", "policy": "maddpg_ceb", "data_source": "live_llm", "final_status": "accepted", "final_answer": "BERT's masked language model objective differs from next sentence prediction in that the masked language model predicts the original vocabulary id of the masked tokens, whereas next sentence prediction tasks aim to understand the relationship between two sentences by predicting whether a sentence is the next sentence after a given sentence or not.", "token_f1": 0.4262, "rouge_l": 0.321, "correctness": 0.4262, "faithfulness": 1.0, "citation_support": 1.0, "source_precision": 1.0, "source_recall": 1.0, "verification_pass": 1, "unsupported_claims": 0, "latency_seconds": 527.7824, "num_llm_calls": 7, "token_usage": 9102, "num_steps": 10, "trace": [{"step": 1, "agent": "retriever", "action": "hybrid_rerank", "params": {"dense_sparse_weight": 0.558147169649601, "top_k": 19, "rerank_threshold": 0.6134103834629059, "source_diversity": 0.264914333820343}, "reward": -0.1191, "done": false}, {"step": 2, "agent": "grader", "action": "strict_filter", "params": {"relevance_threshold": 0.7466092705726624, "evidence_keep_ratio": 0.7527838945388794, "strictness_score": 0.900385320186615}, "reward": -0.3004, "done": false}, {"step": 3, "agent": "generator", "action": "generate_answer", "params": {"temperature": 0.6619608998298645, "citation_strictness": 0.35907958447933197, "max_tokens": 547, "answer_detail_level": 0.5874838456511497}, "reward": -0.3957, "done": false}, {"step": 4, "agent": "verifier", "action": "verify_answer", "params": {"support_threshold": 0.770609587430954, "confidence_threshold": 0.3424