{"question_id": "Q007", "question": "According to Figure 1 in the ResNet paper, what happens to training and test error when moving from a 20-layer plain network to a 56-layer plain network on CIFAR-10?", "ground_truth": "The deeper 56-layer plain network has higher training error and higher test error than the 20-layer plain network.", "category": "figure_table_diagram_grounded", "difficulty": "easy", "policy": "maddpg_ceb", "data_source": "live_llm", "final_status": "accepted", "final_answer": "According to Figure 1, the training and test error on CIFAR-10 with a 56-layer \"plain\" network has higher training error, and thus test error, compared to the 20-layer plain network.", "token_f1": 0.6486, "rouge_l": 0.6415, "correctness": 0.6486, "faithfulness": 1.0, "citation_support": 1.0, "source_precision": 1.0, "source_recall": 1.0, "verification_pass": 1, "unsupported_claims": 0, "latency_seconds": 72.2323, "num_llm_calls": 3, "token_usage": 3423, "num_steps": 4, "trace": [{"step": 1, "agent": "retriever", "action": "hybrid_rerank", "params": {"dense_sparse_weight": 0.5216014217585325, "top_k": 17, "rerank_threshold": 0.6808266043663025, "source_diversity": 0.241085946559906}, "reward": -0.138, "done": false}, {"step": 2, "agent": "grader", "action": "strict_filter", "params": {"relevance_threshold": 0.7738855183124542, "evidence_keep_ratio": 0.736271858215332, "strictness_score": 0.8682013750076294}, "reward": -0.3046, "done": false}, {"step": 3, "agent": "generator", "action": "generate_answer", "params": {"temperature": 0.6204933524131775, "citation_strictness": 0.34274622797966003, "max_tokens": 571, "answer_detail_level": 0.5604216866195202}, "reward": -0.3786, "done": false}, {"step": 4, "agent": "verifier", "action": "verify_answer", "params": {"support_threshold": 0.7650811672210693, "confidence_threshold": 0.4752218872308731}, "reward": 0.5388, "done": true}]}
{"question_id": "Q008", "question": "According to Figure 2 in the ResNet paper, what role does the identity shortcut play in the residual block?", "ground_truth": "The identity shortcut carries the input directly forward and adds it to the learned residual branch, so the block outputs F(x) + x.", "category": "figure_table_diagram_grounded", "difficulty": "medium", "policy": "maddpg_ceb", "data_source": "live_llm", "final_status": "accepted", "final_answer": "The identity shortcut plays the role of performing element-wise addition of the output of the stacked layers to the output of the identity mapping.", "token_f1": 0.2353, "rouge_l": 0.2917, "correctness": 0.2353, "faithfulness": 1.0, "citation_support": 1.0, "source_precision": 1.0, "source_recall": 1.0, "verification_pass": 1, "unsupported_claims": 0, "latency_seconds": 159.2115, "num_llm_calls": 7, "token_usage": 8295, "num_steps": 10, "trace": [{"step": 1, "agent": "retriever", "action": "hybrid_rerank", "params": {"dense_sparse_weight": 0.5218399539589882, "top_k": 17, "rerank_threshold": 0.6832105815410614, "source_diversity": 0.24563607573509216}, "reward": -0.1024, "done": false}, {"step": 2, "agent": "grader", "action": "strict_filter", "params": {"relevance_threshold": 0.7681989967823029, "evidence_keep_ratio": 0.7444496154785156, "strictness_score": 0.8672602772712708}, "reward": -0.3171, "done": false}, {"step": 3, "agent": "generator", "action": "generate_answer", "params": {"temperature": 0.6386521607637405, "citation_strictness": 0.3606744110584259, "max_tokens": 576, "answer_detail_level": 0.5301716290414333}, "reward": -0.4077, "done": false}, {"step": 4, "agent": "verifier", "action": "verify_answer", "params": {"support_threshold": 0.7649134397506714, "confidence_threshold": 0.423343226313591}, "reward": -0.5161, "done": false}, {"step": 5, "agent": "verifier", "action": "request_rewrite", "params": {"support_threshold": 0.7558638155460358, "confidence_threshold": 0.45862341299653053}, "reward":